					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1169503#post-2270870</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1169503/scp-2675#post-2270870</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2015 06:33:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Petrograd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>455145</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Man, now I kinda want to see all the crazy naval SCPs go at it.</p> <p>2675, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1264">SCP-1264</a>, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2846">SCP-2846 A</a> with B and <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1245">1245</a> in hot pursuit, maybe <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1522">1522</a> and <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-455">455</a> pre-wrecking for flavor, and maybe some Final Countdown-style extradimensional shenanigans from <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2120">2120</a>, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2220">2220</a> and <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2069">2069</a>.</p> <p>I might even write it, if I can convince my nautically-obsessed brother to read all of the articles and give me pointers.</p> <p>Edit: Also, +1!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
